---
description: CodeWalker project conventions for contributors and AI agents working on this codebase
alwaysApply: false
globs: "**/*.{ts,tsx,py}"
---

CodeWalker project conventions:

- Use functional and declarative patterns. Avoid classes unless required by the VS Code API (e.g. WebviewViewProvider).
- Prefer pure functions that don't mutate inputs or global state.
- Use ES modules with destructured imports: `import { foo } from 'bar'`.
- Indent with 2 spaces. Omit semicolons in TypeScript.
- Keep functions under 50 lines. Use early returns and guard clauses.
- Name files in kebab-case, functions and variables in camelCase, types and classes in PascalCase.
- Every provider must implement `getReport()` for cross-provider context sharing.
- Python skill scripts read JSON from stdin and write JSON to stdout. No interactive prompts.
- Skill results always return `{ success: boolean, data: object | null, error?: string }`.
- Test with `npm test` (extension unit tests) and `npm run test:e2e` (Playwright E2E).
- Run `npm run compile` before committing — the CI gate will fail on type errors.
